  "prompt": "What are some good romantic movies with unusual ideas?",
  "response": "If you're looking for romantic movies with unique and unconventional ideas, here are some recommendations that might pique your interest:\n\n1. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)**\n   - **Plot**: After a painful breakup, Clementine undergoes a procedure to erase memories of her ex, Joel. When Joel discovers this, he decides to undergo the same procedure. As his memories fade, he tries to cling to the moments they shared, questioning the nature of love and memory.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The film blends science fiction with romance, exploring the concept of erasing memories to cope with heartbreak.\n\n2. **The Lobster (2015)**\n   - **Plot**: In a dystopian society, single people are given 45 days to find a romantic partner, or else they are transformed into animals of their choice. A man, who chooses to become a lobster, navigates this bizarre world while questioning the nature of love and companionship.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The dark comedy and surreal premise challenge traditional views on relationships and societal pressures.\n\n3. **Her (2013)**\n   - **Plot**: Theodore, a lonely writer, develops a relationship with Samantha, an advanced operating system with a charming voice. As their bond deepens, they explore the complexities of love and intimacy in a digital age.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The film delves into the possibility of human-AI relationships, raising questions about connection and emotional fulfillment.\n\n4. **The Science of Sleep (2006)**\n   - **Plot**: St\u00e9phane, a creative but introverted man, struggles to differentiate between dreams and reality as he falls for his neighbor, St\u00e9phanie. Their relationship is woven through surreal, dream-like sequences.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The film blurs the lines between reality and fantasy, using imaginative visuals to explore the connection between dreams and love.\n\n5. **Palm Springs (2020)**\n   - **Plot**: Nyles and Sarah find themselves trapped in a time loop, reliving the same wedding day over and over. As they navigate the endless repetition, they form a bond and explore the meaning of life and love.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The time loop concept adds a comedic and philosophical twist to the rom-com genre.\n\n6. **Wristcutters: A Love Story (2006)**\n   - **Plot**: After committing suicide, Zia finds himself in a bizarre afterlife reserved for people who have taken their own lives. He embarks on a journey to find his ex-girlfriend, meeting other lost souls along the way.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The dark humor and unique setting of a purgatory for suicides offer a fresh take on a romantic quest.\n\n7. **Warm Bodies (2013)**\n   - **Plot**: In a post-apocalyptic world, a zombie named R falls in love with Julie, a human survivor. Their relationship begins to change him and the world around them, challenging the boundaries between life and death.\n   - **Why it's unusual**: The film combines romance with a zombie apocalypse, exploring themes of humanity and transformation.\n\nThese films offer fresh perspectives on love and relationships, making them stand out in the romantic genre.",
